{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-projects-page-js","path":"/projects/mapping-black-sculpture/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Towards the end of my time working at the Museum, a small database project came up for one of\nthe Keepers of museum collections - Vicky Avery. She had been awarded funding to develop a database of\nsculptures representing Black people in museum collections in the United Kingdom. To enable this, I\nimplemented:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>an Omeka S project website (only internal usage until research reaches critical mass), which</li>\n</ul>\n<p>enabled data collection</p>\n<ul>\n<li>IIIF images</li>\n<li>a logical CIDOC CRM mapped schema</li>\n<li>links to people and other entities</li>\n<li>mapping of objects to their current locations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 2000px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.400000000000006%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/4be29/mappingSculpture.webp 500w,\n/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/03f31/mappingSculpture.webp 1000w,\n/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/b1218/mappingSculpture.webp 2000w,\n/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/eb2de/mappingSculpture.webp 2880w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/d1f95/mappingSculpture.jpg 500w,\n/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/dbdff/mappingSculpture.jpg 1000w,\n/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/109c0/mappingSculpture.jpg 2000w,\n/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/ac12e/mappingSculpture.jpg 2880w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/2404a990c1c23721bd4e2d3424f0ee69/109c0/mappingSculpture.jpg\"\n            alt=\"A screenshot from Omeka S\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A screenshot from Omeka S</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>There's not much I can say about this project, as the content was in development when I left. Once the Omeka S database was\nassembled, the plan was to use the API in the same way as we did for the <a href=\"https://amor.fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk\">Hayley Papers project</a> and\nbuild a front end with some great UX and UI work.</p>\n<p>It could end up being a very crucial piece of scholarship.</p>","id":"fc2ffba4-5e80-530a-81a2-54981617712c","timeToRead":1,"wordCount":{"words":162},"frontmatter":{"date":"June 20, 2022","section":"projects","title":"Mapping Black Sculpture","description":"A project to map the locations of black sculpture in the UK","role":null,"partners":null,"collaborators":["Vicky Avery","Dawnanna Kreeger"],"institution":"The Fitzwilliam Museum","publications":null,"geo_lat":52.199722,"geo_lon":0.119167,"news":null,"background":{"id":"fa3756cb-9a84-569f-84ef-a68db2dd490d","absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/museologi.st/museologi.st/content/images/2022/09/IMG_20191219_114201.jpg","publicURL":"/static/5b2a9c1e31231e7a5aef798a7e48450f/IMG_20191219_114201.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#382818","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/5b2a9c1e31231e7a5a